---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Words from Brewing — Beer Terms That Score Big"
  description="Brewing and beer words valid in Scrabble with full scoring. YEAST 8pts, WORT 7pts, STOUT 5pts, HOPS 9pts. Brewery vocabulary for competitive Scrabble players."
  keywords="scrabble brewing words, beer scrabble terms, yeast scrabble points, wort scrabble, hops scrabble word, stout scrabble, brewery words scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words from Brewing — Beer Terms That Score Big","description":"Brewing and beer words valid in Scrabble with full scoring. YEAST 8pts, WORT 7pts, STOUT 5pts, HOPS 9pts.","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-from-brewing"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Is WORT a valid Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! WORT scores 7 points (W=4, O=1, R=1, T=1). It's the sweet liquid extracted from mashing grain, which becomes beer after fermentation. The W tile (4pts) makes this short 4-letter word surprisingly valuable."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How many points is HOPS worth in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"HOPS scores 9 points (H=4, O=1, P=3, S=1). The flowers of the hop plant used to add bitterness to beer. The H (4pts) and P (3pts) combine for a strong 4-letter score."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is YEAST valid in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. YEAST scores 8 points (Y=4, E=1, A=1, S=1, T=1) and is the microorganism that ferments sugars into alcohol. The Y tile (4pts) provides most of the scoring power."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1"><a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span></nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words from Brewing — Beer Terms That Score Big</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400"><time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>5 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a></div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Brewing vocabulary is a hidden gem for Scrabble players. Short, punchy words like WORT and HOPS pack surprising point totals thanks to premium consonants like W, H, and P. Best of all, these are everyday words — no obscure memorisation required.</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">9 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">HOPS (Top)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">8 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">YEAST</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">7 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">WORT</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">5 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">STOUT</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top-Scoring Brewing Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Top Scorer</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">HOPS — 9 Points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">H=4, O=1, P=3, S=1 · 4 letters · H+P combo</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">The cone-shaped flowers used to bitter and flavour beer. At 9 points from just 4 tiles (2.25 per tile), HOPS is one of the most efficient short words available. The H and P tiles together deliver 7 of those 9 points.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🍺 YEAST</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">8 pts · Y=4, E=1, A=1, S=1, T=1 · Fermenting agent</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🫗 WORT</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">7 pts · W=4, O=1, R=1, T=1 · Unfermented beer liquid</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🍻 STOUT</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">5 pts · S=1, T=1, O=1, U=1, T=1 · Dark strong beer</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🌾 MALT</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">6 pts · M=3, A=1, L=1, T=1 · Germinated grain</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">More Brewery Vocabulary</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">LAGER</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">6pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">CASK</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">10pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">BREW</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">9pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">DRAFT</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">9pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">GRAIN</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">6pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">FLASK</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">12pts</span></span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy for Brewing Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">WORT is a W-tile saver:</span> When stuck with a W (4pts), WORT needs only O, R, T — three of the most common tiles in the bag. It's almost always playable.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">HOPS hooks to HOPSCOTCH concepts:</span> While HOPSCOTCH isn't valid, HOPS extends to HOPPED, HOPPER, HOPPING. Use HOPS as a base for future plays.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">YEAST covers the Y tile:</span> Y (4pts) can be tricky to place. YEAST uses it alongside four 1-point tiles (E, A, S, T) — all extremely common. Reliable Y dump.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Brewing words excel at using <span class="text-white font-medium">W, H, and P tiles</span> — three consonants that often get stranded in your rack. WORT, HOPS, and BREW give you reliable 7-9 point plays using just 4 tiles each.</p>
      </div>
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-tea/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Tea</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-horticulture/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Horticulture</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-beekeeping/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Beekeeping</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find every valid brewing word instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center"><a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a></div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
